dfischer.utils

Class ErrorStatusTypeTranslationTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.ErrorStatusTypeTranslationTable

  • public class ErrorStatusTypeTranslationTable
extends java.lang.Object
    A translation table which supports to override information texts for one or several error status types.
    Note: the main purpose of this class is to allow load test plug-ins to create own defined error messages by overriding the information texts for the status types STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_0 up to STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_9.
    See Also:
    LoadtestPluginContext.markUrlAsFailed(int specificErrorStatusType, String specificErrorMessage), PerformanceData.setErrorStatusTypeTranslation(int errorStatusType, String errorStatusTypeText), PerformanceData.getErrorStatusTypeTranslationTable(), HttpTestURL.statusTypeToString(int statusType, ErrorStatusTypeTranslationTable translationTable), HttpTestURL.getErrorTypeString(ErrorStatusTypeTranslationTable translationTable)

      • put

        public boolean put(int errorStatusType,
          java.lang.String errorStatusTypeText)
        Allows to override the information text of an error status type.
        Note: the information text for a particular error status type can be overriden only once during a load test and remain after that constant until the load test job is completed.
        Parameters:
        errorStatusType - the error status type
        errorStatusTypeText - the new information text of the error status type
        Returns:
        true if the information text of the error status type was overriden, or false if a overriden information text for this status type already exists.
        See Also:
        HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_WRONG_HTTP_STATUS, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_WRONG_MIME_TYPE, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_WRONG_CONTENT_SIZE, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_NO_CONTENT_RECEIVED, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_CONTENT_STRING_NOT_FOUND, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_UNEXPECTED_CONTENT_STRING_FOUND, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_USER_SPECIFIC_TEST_FAILED, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_HEADER_STRING_NOT_FOUND, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_UNEXPECTED_HEADER_STRING_FOUND, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_ABORTED_BY_INLINE_SCRIPT, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_0, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_1, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_2, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_3, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_4, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_5, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_6, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_7, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_8, HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_9

      • calcSyntheticErrorStatusType

        public static int calcSyntheticErrorStatusType(java.lang.Throwable t)
        Calculates for an unique Java stack trace a unique error status type (int value). Note that this method always generate values that are greater than HttpTestURL.STATUS_TYPE_PLUGIN_ERROR_CODE_9.
        Parameters:
        t - the Error or Exception from which the unique Java stack trace is taken.
        Returns:
        a unique error status type
